	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>As you pull a glove over your hand, a magical hand appears in the air. As you move your hand, the arcane hand mimics your hand's movement, allowing you to grab, attack, and move things from afar.</em></p><p><strong>Summoning Spell</strong></p><p>You summon a magical hand that mimics your own hand's movement. You must have a free hand to use this spell.</p><ul><li><p>It is a large &amp;reference[construct]{construct}.</p></li><li><p>It has a flying speed of 60 ft.</p></li><li><p>It has AC 13, 60 hit points,* and all its ability scores are 2, except &amp;reference[strength]{strength}, which is 22, and &amp;reference[dexterity]{dexterity} and &amp;reference[constitution]{constitution}, which are 10.</p></li><li><p>It is immune to &amp;reference[poison]{poison} and &amp;reference[psychic]{psychic} damage, and immune to the &amp;reference[poisoned]{poisoned}, &amp;reference[unconscious], and &amp;reference[exhaustion]{exhaustion} conditions.</p></li><li><p>It uses your senses, and might count as &amp;reference[blinded] to something you can't see.</p></li><li><p>It can make an attack when you summon it:</p></li><li><p><strong>Melee Attack</strong> - 1 Creature (5 ft.)</p><ul><li><p><strong>Attack Bonus:</strong> +10</p></li><li><p><strong>Hit:</strong> [[/damage 2d10 + 6 force]] damage.* If the target is huge or smaller, the hand can choose to either push the target 15 ft. or &amp;reference[grappled]{grapple} the target. The hand can only have one creature grappled at a time.</p></li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:rgb(93, 20, 43) rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\"><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:rgb(93, 20, 43) rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);margin:0.5em 0px\"><span style=\"font-family:'Roboto Condensed', sans-serif\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:rgb(93, 20, 43) rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\">Concentration:</strong> Once on each subsequent turn, you can use a bonus action to move the hand and attack with it.</span></p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 1d10 force]]{1d10} for each spell level above 5th.</p>",
